Mexican Stocks: Grupo Aeromexico, Grupo Mexico Shares Advance

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-05-24T21:04:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/mexican-stocks-grupo-aeromexico-grupo-mexico-shares-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 0.5 percent to 35,382.56.  Grupo Aeromexico SAB (AEROMEX* MM) jumped 4.4 percent to
29.15 pesos. The Mexican airline was rated “buy” in new
coverage at Corp. Actinver SAB, according to an e-mailed
statement. Separately, Mexico’s largest airline said late
yesterday that passenger check-in, ticketing and call center
operations were working “satisfactorily” after earlier delays
and cancelations of flights related to the implementation of new
technology.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, advanced 1.6 percent to 40 pesos. Copper futures
for July delivery rose as much as 1.7 percent on the Comex in
 New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
